      },
      {
        "step_no": 3,
        "text": "Season salmon: pat fillets dry, drizzle with remaining oil, sprinkle with remaining salt and pepper, lemon zest, and optional red pepper flakes. Place fillets skin-side down on the other side of the sheet pan leaving space between pieces.",
        "time_min": 3
      },
      {
        "step_no": 4,
        "text": "Roast both salmon and asparagus in the preheated oven until asparagus is tender-crisp and salmon reaches opaque flakiness (salmon should register 125–130°F / 52–54°C for medium-rare to medium). Rotate pan once halfway through if necessary.",
        "time_min": 12
      },
      {
